{"session_id":"019b40ff-0cc1-7f93-a6f4-8aa859c7d6f3","ts":1766322241,"text":"It looks good so far"}
{"session_id":"019b40ff-0cc1-7f93-a6f4-8aa859c7d6f3","ts":1766322279,"text":"It is still ok"}
{"session_id":"019b40ff-0cc1-7f93-a6f4-8aa859c7d6f3","ts":1766322300,"text":"C"}
{"session_id":"019b40ff-0cc1-7f93-a6f4-8aa859c7d6f3","ts":1766322464,"text":"It should have an easy to use UI which looks modern. The media are in the focus. Loading of the page shall be within 5-10 Seconds. Switching blog entries in less than a second and switching trips may take around 2-5 seconds. We do not need offline functions and uploading media can be a single file or even multiple files (more relevant)."}
{"session_id":"019b40ff-0cc1-7f93-a6f4-8aa859c7d6f3","ts":1766322628,"text":"The user wants to be part of the travel, at least virtually. So it should show the trip in nice quality, media in focus. But still enough information to check where the author currently is on his trip. Typical viewers will take only a few minutes to see one new blog entry. So it should show most information on one page. The number of entries per trip are equal to the days. So a typical trip will be at least 1 week and maybe up to 5 weeks. Each blog entry will have text for around 1 page and arpiund 10-15 media files."}
{"session_id":"019b40ff-0cc1-7f93-a6f4-8aa859c7d6f3","ts":1766322652,"text":"C"}
{"session_id":"019b40ff-0cc1-7f93-a6f4-8aa859c7d6f3","ts":1766322861,"text":"The user nneds to log in. After installation or starting the first time the admin user will be created. This user can create more users if required.. Each user will have a username and a password. It is common to use the email adress as username. A user can have the role \"viewer\" or \"creator\". As creator the user can create new trips. After this step the user is also owner of this trip. Then other users can be added to the trip eiter as viewer or as co-creator. As co-creator the user may add own blog entries, edit exsting ones of this trip or even delete blog entries. However, the co-creator can not create new trips or delete a trip."}
{"session_id":"019b40ff-0cc1-7f93-a6f4-8aa859c7d6f3","ts":1766322982,"text":"Just to make it more clear. The user added to the system can be either creator or viewer. If a user is creator he can add and remove trips and also edit everything. As viewer the user can not do this. But a creator can add a user with role viewer to a trip. Then this user can see the trip but not change anything. If the create and owner of the trip enables the viewer to contribute, then the viewer may also add own blog entries and edit existing ones."}
{"session_id":"019b40ff-0cc1-7f93-a6f4-8aa859c7d6f3","ts":1766323007,"text":"C"}
{"session_id":"019b40ff-0cc1-7f93-a6f4-8aa859c7d6f3","ts":1766323074,"text":"C"}
{"session_id":"019b40ff-0cc1-7f93-a6f4-8aa859c7d6f3","ts":1766325961,"text":"The app should be SPA. All common browsers should be supported with current versions. SEO is not required, I want to use it only private with not business behind. Realtime is alos not required, typically I write a new blog entry and then the user can refresh and see it. No special requirements to accessibility."}
{"session_id":"019b40ff-0cc1-7f93-a6f4-8aa859c7d6f3","ts":1766325976,"text":"C"}
{"session_id":"019b40ff-0cc1-7f93-a6f4-8aa859c7d6f3","ts":1766326152,"text":"I would choose 3. The MVP can be without user management, so I can play around myself and my best friends (they will not destroy anything). It is required to add trips and blog entries per trip with text and media. So user management can wait for later phases, as well as map features and coordinate extraction from photos."}
{"session_id":"019b40ff-0cc1-7f93-a6f4-8aa859c7d6f3","ts":1766326182,"text":"C"}
{"session_id":"019b40ff-0cc1-7f93-a6f4-8aa859c7d6f3","ts":1766326285,"text":"1. Plan also phase 2 and 3, 2. a shared link can be used for the phase 1. So the user management can be later."}
{"session_id":"019b40ff-0cc1-7f93-a6f4-8aa859c7d6f3","ts":1766326315,"text":"C"}
{"session_id":"019b40ff-0cc1-7f93-a6f4-8aa859c7d6f3","ts":1766326451,"text":"Security can be basic, so no sepcial requirements. Scalability: keep it simple. I expect 4-5 viewers, max. 15. From these viewers not more than 2-3 will be at the same time."}
{"session_id":"019b40ff-0cc1-7f93-a6f4-8aa859c7d6f3","ts":1766326464,"text":"C"}
